==English==
===Etymology===
Old English [[heahweg|hēahweġ]] ‘road between towns’, corresponding to [[high]] + [[way]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈhaɪweɪ/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A main, direct, [[public]] [[road]].
# A multi-lane, high speed thoroughfare connecting major population centers.

